WEBVTT

00:02.030 --> 00:03.680
<i>* MTV *</i>

00:03.880 --> 00:08.450
<i>* slow, melancholy music *</i>

00:08.650 --> 00:10.840
<i>***</i>

00:25.650 --> 00:27.890
[insects buzzing]

00:29.430 --> 00:31.560
[flames crackling]

00:57.720 --> 01:00.890
<i>***</i>

01:08.660 --> 01:11.900
You suppose I did something
to make the Almighty angry?

01:13.300 --> 01:15.370
He just teaching you.

01:16.410 --> 01:18.720
[scoffs] That I ain't a farmer?

01:18.920 --> 01:22.580
Or that it's hard
and takes patience.

01:23.380 --> 01:26.080
Patience ain't gonna put money
in our pocket.

01:27.480 --> 01:29.650
[flames crackling]

01:36.930 --> 01:38.960
I ain't about to quit this.

01:42.430 --> 01:44.480
<i>* strong, melancholy music *</i>

01:44.680 --> 01:46.670
<i>***</i>

02:15.560 --> 02:17.530
<i>***</i>

02:46.560 --> 02:48.600
[birds singing]

02:50.130 --> 02:52.590
<i>* slow, contemplative music *</i>

02:52.790 --> 02:54.720
[chicken clucking]

02:54.920 --> 02:58.210
<i>***</i>

03:15.960 --> 03:18.190
[insects trilling]

03:23.070 --> 03:24.630
Step up.

03:25.400 --> 03:29.100
Come on around. Come on around.

03:30.670 --> 03:32.710
[insects trilling]

03:54.200 --> 03:55.660
Whoa.

04:03.270 --> 04:06.260
I suspect you know who I am?

04:06.460 --> 04:10.300
Don't matter, seeing as
you're fixing to tell me.

04:10.500 --> 04:13.280
Name is Sherrill Lynn.

04:14.120 --> 04:16.320
Deputy U.S. Marshal.

04:19.020 --> 04:21.140
About 15 days ago,

04:21.340 --> 04:24.740
me and another deputy,
Horace Lee,

04:24.940 --> 04:28.610
we went to serve a writ
in Choctaw Nation.

04:28.810 --> 04:31.230
[Sherrill clears throat]

04:33.100 --> 04:34.550
[Sherrill spits into cup]

04:34.750 --> 04:39.170
We lit out after this red
named "One Charlie."

04:40.380 --> 04:43.550
Charged with introduction
of whiskey.

04:44.380 --> 04:48.000
One Charlie popped Old Horry
right through the lung,

04:48.200 --> 04:51.600
and he lay there
for a good hour or so,

04:51.800 --> 04:54.540
dying... bad.

04:54.740 --> 04:57.740
And I take things like that
personal.

04:57.940 --> 04:59.860
It's a dangerous job.

05:00.900 --> 05:02.680
Judge Parker got his hands full.

05:02.880 --> 05:04.600
He does.

05:05.430 --> 05:08.790
But just yesterday,

05:08.990 --> 05:11.560
we got a lead on an unruly broad

05:11.760 --> 05:15.030
who's putting a roof
over One Charlie's skull.

05:15.230 --> 05:16.330
His wife.

05:16.530 --> 05:19.570
Fiercer
than Mother Nature herself.

05:19.770 --> 05:22.840
And you need somebody
who knows Choctaw.

05:23.040 --> 05:24.840
That...

05:25.040 --> 05:29.290
and someone who could shoot
better than dear old Horace.

05:32.900 --> 05:34.350
What's your offer?

05:34.550 --> 05:37.180
Now, I spoke
with Parker directly.

05:37.380 --> 05:40.390
And he said to sign you up
as a posse man.

05:40.590 --> 05:43.510
- Whose posse man, now?
- Mine.

05:44.870 --> 05:48.710
Appreciate you, Deputy,
but I'm a farmer.

05:57.390 --> 06:00.790
How many mouths you got to feed
with no harvest?

06:11.530 --> 06:13.770
You can keep the cup.

06:27.080 --> 06:29.420
Why not do it?

06:30.850 --> 06:34.440
Figure I got a good reason
right in front of me,

06:34.640 --> 06:37.330
four more upstairs.

06:38.560 --> 06:40.800
Maybe five by tomorrow.

06:43.530 --> 06:46.770
When we had nothing,
we dreamed of everything.

06:48.870 --> 06:51.810
This land, you...

06:53.440 --> 06:56.510
That <i>is</i> everything.

06:57.580 --> 06:59.770
Bass... [chuckles]

06:59.970 --> 07:03.600
A man rode up here
and asked for you.

07:03.800 --> 07:05.200
By name.

07:05.400 --> 07:08.840
A man with an opportunity,
a choice.

07:09.040 --> 07:11.980
[scoffs] We don't get many
of those, now, do we?

07:12.180 --> 07:14.010
A white man with a gun

07:14.210 --> 07:15.550
and all that come with it.

07:15.750 --> 07:19.590
A gun is just a thing,
a tool, an instrument.

07:19.790 --> 07:22.020
What matters is who plays it,
and you Gabriel.

07:22.220 --> 07:25.220
Honey, you only seen me shoot
wild turkeys and feral hogs.

07:25.420 --> 07:27.740
Without a bullet wasted.

07:33.350 --> 07:35.780
I'm content to farm.

07:37.420 --> 07:39.890
I'm free.

07:40.890 --> 07:42.630
Are you?

07:44.760 --> 07:47.810
<i>* majestic music *</i>

07:48.010 --> 07:50.400
<i>***</i>

08:18.860 --> 08:22.210
You got three types of rogues
around these parts.

08:22.410 --> 08:24.620
There's the kind
that steals horses,

08:24.820 --> 08:27.150
the kind that supplies whiskey,

08:27.350 --> 08:31.610
and the kind that's happy to cut
your heart out over both.

08:33.540 --> 08:36.040
Welcome to the Dead Line.

08:37.550 --> 08:39.530
You best load
that antique of yours.

08:39.730 --> 08:44.750
Out here, there ain't no laws,
only outlaws.

08:51.460 --> 08:54.360
[indistinct chatter]

09:07.980 --> 09:09.660
Beautiful.

09:09.860 --> 09:11.730
Excuse me?

09:11.930 --> 09:14.300
The piano, ma'am.
It's beautiful.

09:14.500 --> 09:15.970
You play?

09:16.170 --> 09:18.570
I'm sure your soaps or liniments

09:18.770 --> 09:21.570
or tonics are marvels,
but I don't have time.

09:21.770 --> 09:26.030
Do you have a sense
if it's a boy or a girl?

09:27.800 --> 09:29.720
I have a sense
you want something from me.

09:29.920 --> 09:31.320
No.

09:31.520 --> 09:33.790
I want something <i>for</i> you.

09:33.990 --> 09:37.320
Let us seize the promise
of Reconstruction.

09:37.520 --> 09:39.320
Black paradise.

09:39.520 --> 09:42.330
An entire state to call our own.

09:42.530 --> 09:44.960
There's only one paradise,

09:45.160 --> 09:46.950
and that's the one above.

09:52.760 --> 09:55.740
- [entry bells jingle]
- [laughs softly]

09:55.940 --> 09:59.540
<i>* majestic music *</i>

09:59.750 --> 10:03.470
<i>***</i>

10:06.640 --> 10:08.540
Eyes up, Posse Man.

10:09.340 --> 10:10.940
We're in it now.

10:11.910 --> 10:13.780
Check that mess.

10:19.550 --> 10:21.930
[wind whistling]

10:22.130 --> 10:24.140
<i>* slow, suspenseful music *</i>

10:24.340 --> 10:25.540
<i>***</i>

10:25.740 --> 10:28.060
[horse sputters]

10:32.060 --> 10:34.100
[shallow breathing]

10:35.930 --> 10:38.530
[gasping]

10:44.370 --> 10:46.120
Run.

10:46.320 --> 10:48.980
[gunshots]

10:52.780 --> 10:55.220
[gunshots continue]

11:00.160 --> 11:02.220
[grunts]

11:07.330 --> 11:09.630
[grunts]

11:11.030 --> 11:12.670
Yah!

11:33.190 --> 11:35.220
[birds begin singing]

11:54.210 --> 11:56.240
[horse snorts]

12:19.570 --> 12:22.860
Heavenly Father,

12:23.060 --> 12:27.560
I pray You meet his soul
with Your abundance of love

12:27.760 --> 12:30.600
as he enters
Your Heavenly Kingdom.

12:30.800 --> 12:33.000
[harness jingling]

12:33.200 --> 12:34.850
Amen.

12:43.360 --> 12:44.860
Hmm.

12:48.630 --> 12:50.020
You still believe in a Lord

12:50.220 --> 12:53.190
that let you spend
half your life in chains?

12:53.390 --> 12:55.600
Man made those chains.

12:56.640 --> 12:57.920
It was God who gave me the hope

12:58.120 --> 12:59.760
to believe in a future
without 'em.

12:59.960 --> 13:01.830
Look what hope got him.

13:02.030 --> 13:03.860
Prayers don't hurt.

13:04.060 --> 13:08.350
Yeah. They don't help much,
neither.

13:09.350 --> 13:10.970
Let's go.

13:11.170 --> 13:13.840
Where there's one
crooked vulture,

13:14.040 --> 13:15.940
there's soon to be more.

13:16.140 --> 13:18.180
<i>* slow, somber music *</i>

13:18.380 --> 13:20.630
<i>***</i>

13:26.470 --> 13:27.840
[clicks tongue]

13:46.020 --> 13:47.870
[Bass]
<i>That bitter</i>

13:48.070 --> 13:49.510
<i>and hasty nation,</i>

13:49.710 --> 13:52.850
<i>which shall march</i>
<i>through the breadth of the land,</i>

13:53.050 --> 13:56.180
<i>to possess the dwelling places</i>

13:56.380 --> 13:58.270
<i>that are not theirs.</i>

13:59.230 --> 14:02.490
<i>They are terrible and dreadful:</i>

14:02.690 --> 14:07.640
<i>their judgment and their dignity</i>
<i>shall proceed of themselves.</i>

14:08.910 --> 14:12.850
<i>They shall come</i>
<i>all for violence.</i>

14:15.380 --> 14:19.120
<i>Their faces shall sup up</i>
<i>the east wind...</i>

14:20.360 --> 14:23.540
...and they shall gather
the captivity

14:23.740 --> 14:25.990
as the sand.

14:38.110 --> 14:40.340
- [insects trilling]
- [campfire crackling]

14:41.880 --> 14:43.760
[Sherrill]
Not hungry?

14:43.960 --> 14:45.430
[Bass]
Not hungry enough.

14:45.630 --> 14:47.570
[Sherrill] Food gets scarce
around these parts.

14:47.770 --> 14:51.340
Last winter,
I plucked me a crow,

14:51.540 --> 14:52.910
and I got a good taste

14:53.110 --> 14:55.540
of what he was scrounging on
the day before.

14:55.740 --> 14:58.510
You pay me
an extra five dollars,

14:58.710 --> 15:00.910
I'll scrounge you up
something better than crow.

15:01.110 --> 15:03.020
Well, you've got yourself a hell

15:03.220 --> 15:06.030
of an entrepreneurial spirit,
Bass.

15:09.140 --> 15:12.760
Now what I want to see is
some of that mystical bullshit

15:12.960 --> 15:15.110
them savages taught you.

15:16.010 --> 15:18.360
I don't see no savages.

15:18.560 --> 15:20.500
Just men.

15:20.700 --> 15:23.250
No different than you or me.

15:24.020 --> 15:26.540
They're all killers,
all thieves.

15:26.740 --> 15:27.910
That ain't true, Sherrill.

15:28.110 --> 15:29.840
Oh, you want to know the truth?

15:30.040 --> 15:33.980
Thick of fighting, June 1864.

15:34.180 --> 15:38.250
We was sailing the <i>J.R. Williams</i>
up the Arkansas.

15:38.450 --> 15:40.320
Big old sturdy steamboat.

15:40.520 --> 15:44.860
And a whole herd of them
animals, they bushwhacked us.

15:45.060 --> 15:48.160
They had a whole cadre
of, uh, cannons hidden

15:48.360 --> 15:50.330
high back up there
in the timber,

15:50.530 --> 15:52.000
overlooking the river.

15:52.200 --> 15:54.670
The pilot house took
the first ball,

15:54.870 --> 15:56.830
then the boiler,

15:57.040 --> 15:58.870
then the smokestack, and then

15:59.070 --> 16:02.070
we were just all drowning
in the blood and the river.

16:02.270 --> 16:04.940
<i>* slow, suspenseful music *</i>

16:05.140 --> 16:07.760
<i>***</i>

16:12.070 --> 16:15.370
Most of us didn't make it out
of that iron coffin.

16:16.540 --> 16:20.560
And those of us who did,
we didn't get very far.

16:20.760 --> 16:22.530
Watie and his reds,

16:22.730 --> 16:25.910
they were waiting for us
up on the muddy bank.

16:27.080 --> 16:29.320
I was nearly dead myself.

16:30.650 --> 16:33.510
About a half-second
before I got a glimpse

16:33.710 --> 16:36.120
of my eternal damnation...

16:37.960 --> 16:40.750
...pain just as bright
as the sun

16:40.950 --> 16:42.910
just ripped me back into life.

16:43.120 --> 16:46.480
And I've got a knee
on my throat.

16:46.680 --> 16:48.550
And this unruly red bastard,

16:48.750 --> 16:50.860
he's sawing away at my scalp

16:51.060 --> 16:53.660
like he's a goddamn fur trapper.

16:53.860 --> 16:56.040
<i>***</i>

17:04.350 --> 17:07.970
It's hard for a man
to put fear and hate behind him.

17:08.170 --> 17:12.090
Oh, hell, Bass,
I ain't even trying.

17:15.160 --> 17:18.780
Black, white or red,

17:18.980 --> 17:21.400
we all just men.

17:30.910 --> 17:32.410
[Sherrill]
Shit.

17:40.890 --> 17:42.960
[crow cawing]

17:44.730 --> 17:47.100
[insects trilling]

17:48.030 --> 17:50.900
Why this man called
"One Charlie"?

17:52.000 --> 17:54.620
'Cause there ain't
another Charlie like him.

17:54.820 --> 17:57.120
<i>* slow, suspenseful music *</i>

17:57.320 --> 17:59.090
<i>***</i>

17:59.290 --> 18:02.110
- [indistinct chatter]
- [insects buzzing]

18:10.690 --> 18:12.920
[indistinct chatter]

18:23.000 --> 18:25.030
<i>***</i>

18:30.270 --> 18:32.510
[indistinct chatter continues]

18:38.710 --> 18:40.370
You do the serpent's tongue.

18:40.570 --> 18:42.520
I do the roughhouse.

18:43.320 --> 18:45.020
Go on.

18:49.720 --> 18:51.610
<i>* slow, gentle music *</i>

18:51.810 --> 18:54.000
<i>***</i>

18:57.330 --> 18:59.500
[speaking Choctaw]

19:04.370 --> 19:06.070
I see you.

19:07.210 --> 19:09.030
Step aside, Posse Man.

19:09.230 --> 19:10.950
[grunts]

19:12.350 --> 19:14.050
[groans]

19:16.720 --> 19:18.770
Open the goddamn door!

19:18.970 --> 19:21.170
Get more bees with honey,
Sherrill.

19:21.370 --> 19:22.970
Or I might get stung.

19:23.170 --> 19:24.190
- Whoa!
- [clicks]

19:36.740 --> 19:39.070
[chuckling]

20:17.610 --> 20:20.200
Hey, get your damn hands off me!

20:20.400 --> 20:22.050
Let me talk to her.

20:23.020 --> 20:25.790
Just give me
five minutes, alone.

20:28.560 --> 20:30.410
<i>* slow, haunting music *</i>

20:30.610 --> 20:32.790
<i>***</i>

20:34.100 --> 20:36.130
[sighs]

21:51.570 --> 21:53.810
<i>***</i>

21:56.780 --> 21:59.280
[birds singing]

22:15.800 --> 22:18.030
Yes, ma'am.

22:22.500 --> 22:24.760
<i>* slow, gentle music *</i>

22:24.960 --> 22:27.410
<i>***</i>

22:31.810 --> 22:34.150
[insects trilling]

22:47.360 --> 22:48.580
What is it?

22:48.780 --> 22:50.730
Something I've been waiting
to call my own.

23:04.110 --> 23:06.780
Watch the legs now.
She a precious thing.

23:17.060 --> 23:19.330
Get inside, little girl.

23:28.370 --> 23:30.240
What's your name?

23:31.140 --> 23:32.690
Arthur Mayberry, ma'am.

23:32.890 --> 23:35.360
Well, Arthur, get to it.

23:35.560 --> 23:37.780
Yes, ma'am.

23:47.860 --> 23:49.890
[birds singing]

23:52.190 --> 23:54.430
[insects trilling]

24:02.040 --> 24:05.560
She's likely leading us
straight into an ambush.

24:05.760 --> 24:07.490
She ain't.

24:07.690 --> 24:10.310
Ride easy, Sherrill.

24:14.880 --> 24:16.530
[man]
Oh, shit.

24:16.730 --> 24:17.900
[panting]

24:18.100 --> 24:20.170
- Ride hard, Bass!
- Whoa!

24:20.370 --> 24:22.870
<i>* dramatic, energetic music *</i>

24:23.070 --> 24:25.830
<i>***</i>

24:27.230 --> 24:28.500
[horse neighs]

24:30.330 --> 24:31.600
[guns clicking]

24:33.770 --> 24:35.450
Come on out with your hands up.

24:35.650 --> 24:37.560
Might not understand you.

24:37.760 --> 24:39.710
[gunshot]

24:42.540 --> 24:44.310
[bottles clinking]

24:49.650 --> 24:51.590
[Sherrill]
Let's boom back, Bass.

25:03.000 --> 25:05.000
[gunfire continues]

25:06.070 --> 25:07.870
Your arm.

25:09.970 --> 25:12.090
Lay down cover,
and I'll go around back.

25:12.290 --> 25:15.990
You got some brass balls, Bass.

25:16.190 --> 25:17.900
Ready?

25:18.100 --> 25:19.310
Yeah.

25:21.180 --> 25:22.950
[gunshots]

25:36.760 --> 25:38.600
Charlie!

25:40.330 --> 25:42.220
[Charlie]
Dead today, dead tomorrow.

25:42.420 --> 25:44.220
What's the damn difference?!

25:44.420 --> 25:47.410
Dignity, that's what.

25:53.280 --> 25:54.830
Lay them irons down,

25:55.030 --> 25:57.500
and I'll escort you all the way
to Fort Smith myself.

25:57.700 --> 25:59.800
[Charlie] Ah, Sherrill won't
let that happen.

26:00.000 --> 26:01.610
You have my word.

26:01.810 --> 26:04.380
Keep him talking, Bass!

26:04.580 --> 26:08.250
Charlie? Charlie?

26:08.450 --> 26:11.920
<i>* intense, pulsing music *</i>

26:12.120 --> 26:14.400
<i>***</i>

26:44.030 --> 26:47.000
[Charlie screaming]

26:48.470 --> 26:50.450
Charlie?!

26:50.650 --> 26:52.660
- [doorknob rattling]
- Charlie!

26:52.860 --> 26:54.190
[Charlie continues screaming]

26:54.390 --> 26:55.580
Charlie?

26:58.110 --> 26:59.160
Charlie?

26:59.360 --> 27:01.950
Hold on now!

27:05.520 --> 27:07.720
Charlie?

27:09.190 --> 27:11.040
Charlie!

27:11.240 --> 27:15.180
[yelling]

27:15.380 --> 27:17.030
[yelling continues]

27:18.270 --> 27:19.820
What the hell'd you do?!

27:20.020 --> 27:21.120
[Charlie yelling]

27:21.320 --> 27:22.890
Saving us time.

27:23.090 --> 27:24.810
[yelling]

27:27.540 --> 27:30.030
[yelling]

27:30.230 --> 27:32.360
He ain't worth the bullet.

27:32.560 --> 27:35.520
[yelling]

27:41.990 --> 27:44.980
One Less Charlie, I suppose.

27:45.180 --> 27:47.160
[flames crackling]

27:51.070 --> 27:53.100
[insects trilling]

27:57.070 --> 27:59.170
[match strikes]

28:04.610 --> 28:06.500
<i>* gentle, haunting music *</i>

28:06.700 --> 28:08.880
<i>***</i>

28:35.180 --> 28:37.210
<i>***</i>

28:58.670 --> 29:00.900
[distressed lowing]

29:03.170 --> 29:05.210
[quiet growl]

29:06.710 --> 29:08.430
[insects trilling]

29:08.630 --> 29:10.850
[animals lowing]

29:13.150 --> 29:14.330
[low growling]

29:14.530 --> 29:16.850
[animal lowing]

29:32.230 --> 29:34.270
[animal lowing]

29:38.370 --> 29:40.910
[pained lowing]

29:44.380 --> 29:46.910
[growling]

29:47.680 --> 29:50.430
[growling]

29:50.630 --> 29:53.220
[whimpering, barking]

29:54.960 --> 29:57.010
<i>* slow, ominous music *</i>

29:57.210 --> 29:59.190
<i>***</i>

30:01.230 --> 30:04.220
[calf chuffing]

30:04.420 --> 30:07.130
Hush now.

30:13.570 --> 30:15.340
[calf grunts]

30:18.780 --> 30:21.350
<i>***</i>

30:22.750 --> 30:25.790
[yelling echoes]

30:28.620 --> 30:31.160
[Sherrill groans]

30:39.430 --> 30:41.390
Sometimes you got to be judge,

30:41.590 --> 30:44.640
jury and executioner.

30:45.970 --> 30:47.770
Charlie shot first.

30:49.410 --> 30:53.400
If that devil had just done
what I told him to do,

30:53.600 --> 30:57.020
you wouldn't have had to pump
lead into his thick skull.

30:57.750 --> 30:59.600
Better than being a dead one.

30:59.800 --> 31:02.020
Or a poor farmer.

31:08.900 --> 31:12.230
<i>- ***</i>
- [dialogue inaudible]

31:17.500 --> 31:19.740
[Sherrill groaning]

31:20.840 --> 31:23.180
[insects trilling]

31:26.780 --> 31:28.150
[Sherrill groans]

31:33.890 --> 31:35.810
[Sherrill grunts]

31:36.010 --> 31:38.140
You leave here,

31:38.340 --> 31:41.710
don't you be thinking
you gonna get one thin cent

31:41.910 --> 31:43.730
of what I promised you.

31:44.630 --> 31:46.020
That scar on your head?

31:46.220 --> 31:48.340
It's got chains
around your heart.

31:49.300 --> 31:51.870
Spoken from a man who knows.

31:55.610 --> 31:58.910
You like the man
you are, Deputy?

32:02.750 --> 32:05.400
<i>* slow, melancholy music *</i>

32:05.600 --> 32:07.790
<i>***</i>

32:31.380 --> 32:33.610
[cattle lowing]

32:39.250 --> 32:41.490
[insects trilling]

32:54.140 --> 32:56.540
[sighs]

32:57.470 --> 32:59.520
Didn't mean
to disturb you, ma'am.

32:59.720 --> 33:01.660
[chuckles]
And yet, you slip over?

33:01.860 --> 33:04.530
I did see
that your piano needs fixing.

33:04.730 --> 33:07.580
I could maybe help with that.

33:08.680 --> 33:11.200
You're a sweet boy, Arthur,

33:11.400 --> 33:14.270
which is why I'm going
to do you the service of saying,

33:14.470 --> 33:16.490
don't come back here again.

33:17.660 --> 33:19.960
Not till Sally's older.

33:22.360 --> 33:24.880
<i>* slow, tender music *</i>

33:25.080 --> 33:27.770
<i>***</i>

33:29.770 --> 33:31.420
Hmm.

33:31.620 --> 33:34.740
- [indistinct chatter]
- [hawk calling]

34:44.210 --> 34:47.750
- [playing piano slowly]
- [rocking chair creaking]

34:51.750 --> 34:53.840
You're hurting my ears.

34:54.040 --> 34:55.020
[stops playing]

34:56.320 --> 35:00.430
Spare your mama the honesty
just once and come sit with me.

35:12.910 --> 35:14.760
What's so special
about this old thing?

35:14.960 --> 35:19.060
Nothing yet, but you and I are
gonna resurrect it.

35:19.260 --> 35:20.660
Why can't Harriet?

35:20.860 --> 35:23.200
'Cause when you were growing
in my belly,

35:23.400 --> 35:24.970
I played all the time.

35:25.170 --> 35:27.040
- You did?
- Mm-hmm.

35:27.240 --> 35:29.440
Mistress on the plantation
fancied herself kind

35:29.640 --> 35:31.480
by teaching me how.

35:31.680 --> 35:34.310
- I'd never play again, then.
- Mm, see,

35:34.510 --> 35:38.420
the piano was hers,
but the music?

35:38.620 --> 35:40.800
[plays a few chords]

35:42.440 --> 35:45.240
That was all mine.

35:48.110 --> 35:51.460
Always have something
that's yours

35:51.660 --> 35:53.810
and yours alone, baby.

36:06.660 --> 36:09.160
[insects trilling]

36:12.370 --> 36:14.820
<i>* slow, suspenseful music *</i>

36:15.020 --> 36:16.890
<i>***</i>

36:17.090 --> 36:20.240
[bird squawking]

36:30.220 --> 36:32.070
- Daddy!
- Daddy!

36:32.270 --> 36:33.270
- Daddy.
- Dad.

36:33.470 --> 36:34.460
Daddy.

36:41.830 --> 36:43.080
Hi, Bass.

36:43.280 --> 36:45.980
How the one I haven't met?

36:46.180 --> 36:47.950
Restless like my granddaddy.

36:48.150 --> 36:50.950
Thought if he's a boy, we should
name him "Bennie" in his honor.

36:51.150 --> 36:53.340
[Bass chuckles softly]

37:04.590 --> 37:07.740
Man in town tried
to sell me paradise, so,

37:07.940 --> 37:10.590
I bought that piano instead.

37:11.960 --> 37:14.010
With what?

37:14.210 --> 37:15.680
With the promise

37:15.880 --> 37:18.430
that my husband was making
a decent payday.

37:19.230 --> 37:21.520
About that...

37:21.720 --> 37:23.850
About what?

37:24.050 --> 37:25.810
Um...

37:28.380 --> 37:29.830
...I hit another white man.

37:30.030 --> 37:32.310
Not that deputy?

37:34.050 --> 37:36.420
I'm sorry.

37:39.720 --> 37:42.490
I'll figure a way
to pay for the piano.

37:44.260 --> 37:46.630
[sighs]

37:47.590 --> 37:48.800
Hup, hup.

37:51.930 --> 37:54.170
[birds singing]

37:55.000 --> 37:57.190
[chickens clucking]

37:57.390 --> 38:00.670
Come on around. Come on around.

38:02.910 --> 38:04.800
- Step up.
<i>- * dark, suspenseful music *</i>

38:05.000 --> 38:06.510
Whoa.

38:09.320 --> 38:11.990
Take the kids inside!

38:12.720 --> 38:14.410
Get your brother
and sisters in the house.

38:14.610 --> 38:16.810
- But Mama--
- Girl, I'm not asking.

38:17.010 --> 38:18.790
Come on.

38:24.030 --> 38:27.420
No need to puff your chest
in front of my family.

38:27.620 --> 38:28.700
Hmm.

38:29.500 --> 38:31.390
[Sherrill]
Just so we're clear,

38:31.590 --> 38:33.560
I would've done One Charlie
the same way

38:33.760 --> 38:37.330
and not think twice about it
if it meant it was you and I

38:37.530 --> 38:39.430
walking away from there
with air in our lungs.

38:39.630 --> 38:42.300
And I'm not looking
to take anything back, either.

38:42.500 --> 38:44.300
Christ, Bass.

38:44.500 --> 38:48.590
You are the most earnest man
I have ever met.

38:50.360 --> 38:53.290
Which is likely
to get you killed one day.

38:54.160 --> 38:56.630
You got sand for this.

38:57.460 --> 38:59.430
Most men don't.

39:01.400 --> 39:03.120
What you saying?

39:03.320 --> 39:05.260
I had a, uh...

39:05.460 --> 39:07.920
revelation, if you will,

39:08.120 --> 39:12.580
and I took some of your
earnestness to Judge Parker.

39:14.180 --> 39:15.580
And?

39:16.420 --> 39:17.600
And he wants to make you

39:17.800 --> 39:21.140
a goddamn Deputy U.S. Marshal.

39:21.340 --> 39:23.140
<i>* dramatic, swelling music *</i>

39:23.340 --> 39:25.830
<i>***</i>

39:28.030 --> 39:31.970
You think you can handle
the weight of the badge?

39:35.670 --> 39:38.440
[Bass]
I know I can.

39:40.240 --> 39:42.480
[insects trilling]

39:58.360 --> 40:00.560
Hey, handsome.

40:04.000 --> 40:05.520
Sally okay?

40:05.720 --> 40:10.370
Let's just say we got
a whole new wolf to worry about.

40:11.270 --> 40:12.960
- [sighs]
- She'll be fine.

40:13.160 --> 40:14.510
[Jennie chuckles]

40:17.640 --> 40:19.550
She listens to you.

40:20.450 --> 40:23.700
[sighs] She dream
of faraway places.

40:23.900 --> 40:25.740
I can't fault her.

40:25.940 --> 40:29.640
One day, them dreams
gonna take her far away,

40:29.840 --> 40:31.890
and she won't come
back the same.

40:32.890 --> 40:35.250
We didn't.

40:35.450 --> 40:37.710
But our love held strong.

40:37.910 --> 40:39.420
<i>* dramatic, optimistic music *</i>

40:39.620 --> 40:42.490
Hers will, too.
That won't change.

40:42.690 --> 40:43.970
Mm.

40:45.240 --> 40:47.540
God showed us the way.

40:48.840 --> 40:50.040
And now?

40:52.250 --> 40:54.350
Do His will.

40:58.350 --> 41:00.450
Justice.

41:05.130 --> 41:07.360
<i>***</i>

41:19.640 --> 41:24.360
[Parker]
<i>I need a man</i>

41:24.560 --> 41:26.530
with a good gun
and a straight spine.

41:26.730 --> 41:28.280
You up for the task?

41:29.080 --> 41:30.570
[Garrett]
<i>Billy Crow.</i>

41:30.770 --> 41:32.540
<i>Wanted in connection with</i>
<i>a stagecoach robbery.</i>

41:32.740 --> 41:34.400
Well, I can help you
with that, Deputy Reeves.

41:34.610 --> 41:36.520
Gonna hold you to that.

41:37.490 --> 41:38.480
[Parker]
<i>It's hard work.</i>

41:38.680 --> 41:40.280
<i>It exacts a toll.</i>

41:40.480 --> 41:43.330
<i>Few men survive long enough</i>
<i>to be good at it.</i>

41:44.970 --> 41:46.580
You gonna shoot me?

41:46.780 --> 41:48.790
No.

41:48.990 --> 41:50.470
But they will.

41:52.210 --> 41:56.830
<i>* gentle, haunting music *</i>

41:57.030 --> 41:59.010
<i>***</i>
